saltOS live ISO builder

Overview
--------
build-iso.sh assembles a hybrid bootable live ISO from a base rootfs produced by
os/bootstrap. The live image boots into an LXQt session (SDDM autologin) with the
Calamares graphical installer available via an "Install saltOS" desktop launcher.
The builder is parameterized by architecture and supports both x86_64 and aarch64.

Layout
------
build-iso.sh            POSIX sh ISO assembler (squashfs + initramfs + GRUB + xorriso)
grub/grub.cfg.in        GRUB menu template (UEFI on both arches, BIOS on x86_64)
live/live-init          fallback live-boot init (squashfs + overlayfs, toram option)
live/live-setup.sh      live-session setup: live user, SDDM autologin, repo bind mount
live/sv/live-setup/run  runit service that runs live-setup once at boot
live/Install-saltOS.desktop  desktop launcher that runs calamares

Boot model
----------
Bootloader: GRUB. This matches the rollback model in DISTRO.md (GRUB has the best
Btrfs snapshot and previous-deployment boot story) and gives one bootloader across
UEFI for both arches plus BIOS for x86_64.

UEFI: a FAT El Torito image (boot/grub/efiboot.img) holds a standalone GRUB EFI
binary (BOOTX64.EFI on x86_64, BOOTAA64.EFI on aarch64) under EFI/BOOT.
BIOS (x86_64 only): a GRUB i386-pc core image is embedded as an El Torito no-emul
boot image and the ISO is made isohybrid so it boots from USB.

Live filesystem: the rootfs is packed into live/filesystem.squashfs (zstd). At boot
the live init mounts the squashfs read-only and stacks a tmpfs overlay on top so the
running system is writable but the medium stays read-only. A "toram" menu entry copies
the squashfs into RAM and frees the medium. If the rootfs ships dracut with the
dmsquash-live module, build-iso.sh uses dracut for the initramfs; otherwise it builds
a minimal initramfs around live/live-init.

Prerequisites (Linux build host)
--------------------------------
- mksquashfs (squashfs-tools)
- xorriso
- grub-mkstandalone, grub-mkimage and the GRUB platform modules:
    /usr/lib/grub/x86_64-efi, /usr/lib/grub/arm64-efi, /usr/lib/grub/i386-pc
- mkfs.vfat (dosfstools) and mtools (mmd/mcopy) for the EFI image
- optional: dracut in the rootfs for the live initramfs
- a base rootfs from os/bootstrap that already contains the kernel, calamares,
  the salt CLI, LXQt, SDDM, btrfs-progs, grub, and the runit service tree

Usage
-----
x86_64:

    os/iso/build-iso.sh \
        --arch x86_64 \
        --rootfs /path/to/rootfs-x86_64 \
        --repo repo/x86_64 \
        --out saltos-0.1-x86_64.iso

aarch64:

    os/iso/build-iso.sh \
        --arch aarch64 \
        --rootfs /path/to/rootfs-aarch64 \
        --repo repo/aarch64 \
        --out saltos-0.1-aarch64.iso

Options: --version, --label, --kernel (kernel/module version under
<rootfs>/lib/modules; auto-detected when omitted).

The bundled repository (--repo) is placed at /repo on the ISO. live-setup.sh
bind-mounts the live medium's repo to /run/salt/repo, which is the source the
installer's saltos_base module reads when it runs salt install --root.
